VALUES ('d9e03284-0470-4afa-9f6d-89020e767227', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Honeybees communicate the location of food through a movement scientists call the waggle dance. The angle of the dance relative to the hive shows direction, while the duration of the waggle reveals distance. ______ a single dance can tell other bees exactly where to fly.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"In contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: nothing in the final sentence opposes the prior information."},{"id":"B","text":"As a result,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it presents the precise directions as the outcome of encoding direction and distance."},{"id":"C","text":"However,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''However'' signals contrast, but the final sentence continues the same idea."},{"id":"D","text":"Meanwhile,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Wrong: ''Meanwhile'' marks simultaneous events, not a consequence."}]'::jsonb, 'B', 'Step 1 — Identify what the dance encodes
The text explains the dance shows direction and {{yellow:the duration of the waggle reveals distance}}.
Step 2 — Choose the result
Because both direction and distance are conveyed, the bees knowing exactly where to fly is a consequence, so ''As a result'' fits.
Distractor analysis:
- A: ''In contrast'' needs opposing ideas, but the final sentence agrees.
- C: ''However'' marks contrast that is not present.
- D: ''Meanwhile'' marks simultaneous action, not a result.', 'Is the last sentence a consequence of the encoded information or a contrast to it?', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'easy', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
